                What Does This Mean?
            </h1>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="container">
            In short, this means that this webpage was set up to allow for easy access for users (and me lol) to run
            jobs more easily and allow for a repository to be analysed easily through a nice interface. Under the
            "Code Analysis" tab, it's possible to view already mined repositories and submit your own GitHub links
            for <strong>Python</strong> repositories to be mined (as of March 2017). Graphs and other metrics per repo
            should also be visible as a way to see who and what governs the quality of a repository.
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="container">
            To mine a repository, input its URL into the text box, submit it as a job, and then wait. Metric are
            generated on the fly, so graphs will be updated on refresh until all of the commits have been analysed.
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

